Qt Hldplugin version 3.3.1 contains bug fixes.

The most important changes are listed in this document. For a complete
list of changes, see the Git log for the Qt Hldplugin sources that
you can check out from the public Git repository. For example:

git clone git://gitorious.org/qt-hldplugin/qt-hldplugin.git
git log --cherry-pick --pretty=oneline v3.3.0..v3.3.1

Editing
   * Fixed crash with some highlighting files (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-13883)

CMake Projects
   * Fixed include completion (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-13567)
   * Fixed highlighting for CMake files (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-13588)

C++ Support
   * Fixed comment continuation (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-13415)
   * Fixed Convert to Pointer refactoring action for auto variables
     (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-13605)
   * Fixed that triggering refactoring actions from the context menu
     worked only if the text cursor was set first (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-13388)
   * Fixed crash if no kits are available (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-13730)
   * Fixed infinite loop when parsing some files (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-13703)
   * Fixed crash when #if nesting is deeper than 512 levels

Version Control Systems
   * Git
      * Fixed reverting chunks in diff viewer when diff.mnemonicprefix is set
        (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-13782)
   * ClearCase
      * Fixed that check out was requested even though the file was already
        checked out (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-13782)

Code Pasting
   * Fixed pasting to pastebin.ca (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-13802)

Platform Specific

OS X
   * Fixed dropping files from Finder onto Qt Hldplugin (QTBUG-40449)

Android
   * Fixed crash when removing auto-detected kits (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-13736)
   * Fixed debugging applications that link many modules (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-13691)

WinRT
   * Fixed installing custom files into package root (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-13835)
   * Fixed occasional crashes when debugging

